name: Lover Man (Oh Where Can You Be)
Parker's Mood
comments: Parker recorded five takes of "Parker's Mood" at this session -- one with a false start, two which are incomplete, and two that were considered releasable at the time.  This version was actually the fifth take.  All five takes have now been released, but this first.

name: Husbands and Wives
comments: The music is mostly a long improvised duet, which bears no resemblance to "Husbands and Wives".  Toward the end of this twelve minute plus performance, Chadbourne begins singing "Husbands and Wives", and, at that point, the music becomes recognizable as "Husbands and Wives".

name: Au Privave
comments: There were two versions of "Au Privave" recorded at this session.  Both have appeared many times on various compilations; however, the other version was only first released in 1961.
